content.description: Start under roof with right hand jug and left had pinch.  Set feet and make a big move to a good edge.  Move right through pinches and slopers to top-out.   Really fun movement!
content.location: This boulder faces north and sits about 20 north of Elbow Room.

content.description: Start about 5ft. to the left of the Warbler and move across boulder via pocket and foot trickery to finish on the Warbler.  Really cool moves and adds a lot to the existing line.
Start low and left on boulder.  Bump left hand up to small crack and ease up to slopers.  Traverse right along slopey jugs to big finish.
content.location: This boulder is directly to the right(north) of the Elbow Room boulder.

climbs.name: Manta Ray
climbs.fa: Ian CB and Kevin Baker probably

content.description: A pure line, definitely cool, and very unique.  Start hanging from the edge near the arete and surmount the hanging block feature. Hint: We campused left for the first move and threw a heal hook..
content.protection: Four or more pads and a spotter or two.  It feels a bit committing.
content.location: 100 feet north of Fearful Symmetry and the same level on the hillside.

content.description: Start low on jug.  Hike feet and gun big for good edge.  Bump out to slopers and find hidden left crimp.  Top-out.
content.protection: Pads and spotters.  There are a couple trees at the base, and a fall from the top-out would be bad, heads up.
content.location: Arete to the left of Elbow Room.

content.description: Same start as High-Low.  At good edge, bump out to pocket and finish up on Elbow Room.  Fun link-up!
content.location: Low, left start to Elbow Room.

content.description: Start with right hand in slot and left on crimp.  Set left foot and gun for pocket.  A couple more big moves get you to a heady top-out.  Fun!
content.location: This boulder sits about 30ft downhill and north of Fearful Symmetry.  It faces north.

content.description: Climb up the center of the north face of the elbow room boulder starting from a stand with your right hand in a good slanting slot and your left on an undercling.. The first move is deceptively tricky..
content.location: On the elbow room boulder.  Walk straight up the hill 40 feet north of the "Nancy J Holt" bench 300 feet.  This boulder is in the trees above the talus field that runs perpendicular across the hillside.  The warbler boulder is just downhill, the fearful symmetry boulder is uphill and south by 60 feet or so.

content.description: Start low and right on boulder with left hand on arete and right in a slot.  Climb arete to fun top-out.
content.location: Arete to the right of Elbow Room.

content.description: Elbow Room, the Warbler, and Manta Ray are a collection of smaller boulders.
